author: Justin Harp
title: TV show ratings: Arrow and Empire dip on Wednesday - Arrow Cult -
text: Arrow and Empire were both down on Wednesday (October 14), according to Nielsen figures.The DC Comics series fell one-tenth of a point to 1.0 (2.50m) at 8pm on The CW, followed by Supernatural dipping to 0.8 (1.85m) at 9pm. © The CW / Katie Yu Empire earned 4.7 (12.22m) at 9pm on Fox, down three-tenths. Earlier in the night, Rosewood hit 1.4 (5.03m) at 8pm.Fox still won the key 18-49 demographic on Wednesday with 3.0.Over on ABC, The Middle garnered 2.0 (7.12m) at 8pm, The Goldbergs took 2.0 (6.35m) at 8.30pm, Modern Family averaged 2.7 (7.88m) at 9pm, and Black-ish attracted 1.8 (5.66m) at 9.30pm. © Channel 4 / Lionsgate Nashville was steady at 10pm on ABC, pulling in 1.1 (4.54m).Survivor rose a tenth to 2.2 (9.07m) at 8pm on CBS, before Criminal Minds and Code Black generated 1.7 (9.08m) at 9pm and 1.2 (6.96m) at 10pm.NBC's The Mysteries of Laura scored 1.0 (6.92m) at 8pm. Law & Order: SVU and Chicago PD held their ground with 1.5 (6.20m) at 9pm and 1.5 (6.58m) at 10pm.
